1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:04,462
[Carillo] <i>At 1:45 p.m. tomorrow…</i>

2
00:00:04,546 --> 00:00:07,799
You will have to press that button.

3
00:00:07,882 --> 00:00:08,675
[tense music playing]

4
00:00:09,175 --> 00:00:11,803
[Marcus] <i>Lara hasn't reported</i>
<i>to the headquarters for several days.</i>

5
00:00:11,886 --> 00:00:14,597
<i>Lara was suddenly gone</i>
<i>after the explosion.</i>

6
00:00:14,681 --> 00:00:15,849
<i>No one can find her.</i>

7
00:00:15,932 --> 00:00:18,226
Did you have an opportunity
to speak with Lara

8
00:00:18,309 --> 00:00:20,520
before or after the explosion?

9
00:00:20,603 --> 00:00:21,771
Tell me the truth.

10
00:00:21,855 --> 00:00:23,273
[Carillo] <i>Was it you</i>
<i>who activated the detonator?</i>

11
00:00:23,857 --> 00:00:24,566
[Felix] <i>Yes, General.</i>

12
00:00:24,649 --> 00:00:27,277
- [screaming]
- [loud thud]

13
00:00:28,361 --> 00:00:30,780
[Felix] <i>Don't you dare mess up, Lara.</i>

14
00:00:31,489 --> 00:00:33,116
I don't want to kill you.

15
00:00:37,954 --> 00:00:41,082
[Lara] <i>Why am I doing this?</i>
<i>Because you killed my parents, that's why!</i>

16
00:00:41,166 --> 00:00:43,168
<i>1997! Cabatangon Medical Mission!</i>

17
00:00:43,251 --> 00:00:46,379
<i>I saw how you killed my parents!</i>

18
00:00:46,463 --> 00:00:48,214
[Datu Rahman] <i>It was all</i>
<i>Colonel Marcelino's plan.</i>

19
00:00:48,298 --> 00:00:51,634
He ordered the attack
on the medical mission.

20
00:00:51,718 --> 00:00:53,094
[Datu Rahman] <i>My real name is Hassan Wadi.</i>

21
00:00:53,178 --> 00:00:57,348
<i>I changed my name</i>
<i>to escape Colonel Marcelino's group.</i>

22
00:00:57,432 --> 00:00:58,683
<i>Please forgive me, Jamilah.</i>

23
00:00:58,767 --> 00:01:02,979
<i>I didn't tell the whole truth</i>
<i>to you and Jalil.</i>

24
00:01:03,063 --> 00:01:05,982
[Dante] <i>It was Manuel</i>
<i>who killed your parents, Lara.</i>

25
00:01:06,066 --> 00:01:09,027
<i>He was the mastermind behind that attack.</i>

26
00:01:09,110 --> 00:01:11,488
<i>He wanted to frame the Muslim rebels.</i>

27
00:01:11,571 --> 00:01:14,491
[Ahmad] <i>Lara is the weakest link</i>
<i>in Carillo's group.</i>

28
00:01:14,574 --> 00:01:15,658
You need to find her.

29
00:01:15,742 --> 00:01:19,454
Because if my hunch is right,
her life is in danger.

30
00:01:19,537 --> 00:01:21,831
[screaming]

31
00:01:23,041 --> 00:01:25,502
[Lara] <i>You've kept</i>
<i>so many secrets from me, Dad.</i>

32
00:01:28,379 --> 00:01:30,089
<i>I'll make you pay.</i>

33
00:01:33,968 --> 00:01:40,266
[theme music playing]

34
00:01:49,150 --> 00:01:50,485
Raquel, you're done for the day.

35
00:01:50,568 --> 00:01:52,028
Take a rest.

36
00:01:52,112 --> 00:01:53,363
Are you sure, General?

37
00:01:53,446 --> 00:01:55,323
Yes, I'll be here for a while longer.

38
00:01:55,406 --> 00:01:57,117
Oh, alright.

39
00:01:57,659 --> 00:01:59,035
Thank you, General.

40
00:02:01,246 --> 00:02:02,330
[Raquel sighs]

41
00:02:03,289 --> 00:02:09,254
[ominous music playing]

42
00:02:10,922 --> 00:02:13,091
[Carillo sighs]

43
00:02:37,532 --> 00:02:39,033
Good evening, ma'am.

44
00:02:45,665 --> 00:02:47,125
[bodyguard 1] Good evening, ma'am.

45
00:02:49,794 --> 00:02:51,296
[bodyguard 2] Good evening, ma'am.

46
00:02:57,635 --> 00:03:00,597
[men grunting]

47
00:03:02,557 --> 00:03:09,022
[suspenseful music playing]

48
00:03:21,659 --> 00:03:24,662
[Carillo]
Raquel, didn't I tell you to take a rest?

49
00:03:28,166 --> 00:03:28,917
[gun cocks]

50
00:03:29,959 --> 00:03:32,503
[suspenseful music continues]

51
00:03:57,320 --> 00:04:01,824
[Lara breathing heavily]

52
00:04:05,662 --> 00:04:07,497
What did I teach you, Lara?

53
00:04:10,375 --> 00:04:13,753
A gun, when pointed…

54
00:04:14,462 --> 00:04:17,257
you have to be ready to fire.

55
00:04:17,882 --> 00:04:20,009
You've been lying to me for so long!

56
00:04:20,093 --> 00:04:21,970
Huh? You've been lying to me for so long!

57
00:04:22,053 --> 00:04:25,014
I saved you from the syndicate!

58
00:04:25,098 --> 00:04:28,017
I took you in, trained you,
gave you direction!

59
00:04:28,101 --> 00:04:29,602
And for what?

60
00:04:29,686 --> 00:04:30,979
Huh? For what?

61
00:04:31,062 --> 00:04:32,772
To wash away your sins?!

62
00:04:32,855 --> 00:04:35,316
To put you on the right side of history

63
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:36,359
- beside me!
- No!

64
00:04:36,442 --> 00:04:37,986
No! No!

65
00:04:39,279 --> 00:04:40,530
Stop it! No!

66
00:04:40,613 --> 00:04:44,158
You did that because you were using me!

67
00:04:44,242 --> 00:04:45,785
You used me!

68
00:04:45,868 --> 00:04:48,663
You used my parents' death!

69
00:04:49,706 --> 00:04:53,501
You used my desire to avenge my parents!

70
00:04:53,584 --> 00:04:55,044
For what, huh?

71
00:04:55,128 --> 00:04:56,921
You wanted me to be a loyal soldier?

72
00:04:57,005 --> 00:04:58,923
You wanted me to be a blind follower?

73
00:04:59,007 --> 00:05:01,009
You killed my parents, didn't you?!

74
00:05:01,092 --> 00:05:03,511
I didn't kill them!

75
00:05:03,594 --> 00:05:06,556
This broken system we're fighting…

76
00:05:06,639 --> 00:05:08,933
- Enough!
- This is what killed your parents!

77
00:05:09,017 --> 00:05:10,393
Enough! You're insane!

78
00:05:10,476 --> 00:05:11,769
[Lara] You're insane! Insane!

79
00:05:11,853 --> 00:05:13,104
- [Lara] You're insane!
- Lara!

80
00:05:13,187 --> 00:05:16,024
[suspenseful music continues]

81
00:05:23,740 --> 00:05:26,743
[somber music playing]

82
00:05:29,495 --> 00:05:30,788
Don't do it.

83
00:05:34,042 --> 00:05:35,209
[Felix] Please.

84
00:05:35,293 --> 00:05:36,419
[Lara sighs]

85
00:05:37,795 --> 00:05:40,214
[sobbing] Lara, please.

86
00:05:42,175 --> 00:05:44,260
Don't. Don't do it.

87
00:05:48,765 --> 00:05:50,099
[sobbing] Don't do it.

88
00:06:06,991 --> 00:06:08,868
[whimpering]

89
00:06:08,951 --> 00:06:10,203
[sniffles]

90
00:06:17,210 --> 00:06:18,377
Don't.

91
00:06:21,422 --> 00:06:22,757
[suspenseful music stops]

92
00:06:23,341 --> 00:06:26,719
[sobbing]

93
00:06:29,555 --> 00:06:30,932
[Lara sniffs]

94
00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:43,027
[breathes deeply]

95
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:48,449
[somber music playing]

96
00:06:48,533 --> 00:06:50,493
[Felix sobbing]

97
00:06:50,576 --> 00:06:51,786
Lara, please.

98
00:06:51,869 --> 00:06:53,287
[Lara sighs]

99
00:07:37,331 --> 00:07:39,500
[crying]

100
00:07:39,584 --> 00:07:42,753
Lara…

101
00:07:43,921 --> 00:07:45,798
Lara!

102
00:07:46,382 --> 00:07:47,925
Lara!

103
00:07:48,634 --> 00:07:49,886
Lara!

104
00:07:49,969 --> 00:07:52,513
[screaming] Lara…

105
00:07:52,597 --> 00:07:56,142
[Carillo crying]

106
00:07:56,225 --> 00:07:59,103
[dramatic music continues]

107
00:07:59,187 --> 00:08:05,109
[Carillo crying heavily]

108
00:08:08,070 --> 00:08:12,283
- [crying] Lara…
- [Felix sobbing]

109
00:08:12,867 --> 00:08:16,579
[crying]

110
00:08:17,955 --> 00:08:19,916
Lara…

111
00:08:19,999 --> 00:08:22,752
[Carillo] Lara…

112
00:08:22,835 --> 00:08:27,131
- [Carillo crying]
- [Felix breathing heavily]

113
00:08:32,053 --> 00:08:33,513
[Raquel] General?

114
00:08:33,596 --> 00:08:34,430
Gen--

115
00:08:34,514 --> 00:08:36,933
- [crying, wailing]
- [Manuel] Lara…

116
00:08:37,016 --> 00:08:40,520
[wailing] Lara!

117
00:08:40,603 --> 00:08:43,189
[crying, wailing]

118
00:08:43,272 --> 00:08:44,482
[Raquel] Lara!

119
00:08:44,565 --> 00:08:48,569
[crying, wailing]

120
00:08:48,653 --> 00:08:49,820
[Raquel] Lara!

121
00:08:49,904 --> 00:08:51,739
[Felix crying]

122
00:08:51,822 --> 00:08:52,823
Lara!

123
00:08:52,907 --> 00:08:55,618
[crying continues]

124
00:08:56,244 --> 00:08:58,120
[Raquel] Lara…

125
00:08:58,204 --> 00:09:00,540
[sniffles, crying] Lara!

126
00:09:00,623 --> 00:09:02,625
[Felix crying]

127
00:09:02,708 --> 00:09:05,336
[somber music playing]

128
00:09:06,087 --> 00:09:09,340
[unsettling music playing]

129
00:09:09,423 --> 00:09:13,803
- [breathes heavily]
- [beeping sound]

130
00:09:27,275 --> 00:09:29,068
[sniffles, breath quivers]

131
00:09:38,911 --> 00:09:41,080
[sobbing]

132
00:09:42,123 --> 00:09:44,458
[sniffling, sobbing]

133
00:09:53,676 --> 00:09:55,970
[inhales]

134
00:09:56,887 --> 00:09:58,973
[tense music playing]

135
00:10:15,948 --> 00:10:18,659
[tense music continues]

136
00:11:59,510 --> 00:12:01,220
[Felix crying]

137
00:12:01,303 --> 00:12:06,225
[crying, sobbing]

138
00:12:07,184 --> 00:12:09,311
[crying]

139
00:12:09,395 --> 00:12:11,188
[pensive music playing]

140
00:12:11,272 --> 00:12:12,314
[sniffles]

141
00:12:12,398 --> 00:12:15,568
[crying, sobbing]

142
00:12:15,651 --> 00:12:18,154
[breathing heavily]

143
00:12:18,237 --> 00:12:19,280
Lara…

144
00:12:19,363 --> 00:12:20,281
[Felix sobs]

145
00:12:20,364 --> 00:12:23,075
[tense music playing]

146
00:12:23,159 --> 00:12:27,621
[crying, sobbing]

147
00:12:28,539 --> 00:12:29,790
I'm sorry.

148
00:12:30,666 --> 00:12:31,500
[sniffles]

149
00:12:31,584 --> 00:12:34,336
You just wouldn't listen to me.

150
00:12:35,254 --> 00:12:40,009
[somber music playing]

151
00:12:41,927 --> 00:12:45,639
[crying, sobbing]

152
00:13:15,377 --> 00:13:17,463
[crying, sobbing]

153
00:13:17,546 --> 00:13:20,382
I love you so much, Lara.

154
00:13:20,466 --> 00:13:22,885
[breathing heavily]

155
00:13:22,968 --> 00:13:24,512
You're so stubborn.

156
00:13:24,595 --> 00:13:26,597
[breathing heavily]

157
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:30,392
You were gone.

158
00:13:31,060 --> 00:13:32,061
[breath quivers]

159
00:13:32,645 --> 00:13:35,481
I'm sorry. Please forgive me.

160
00:13:35,564 --> 00:13:41,529
[crying, sobbing]

161
00:13:43,822 --> 00:13:45,491
[screams]

162
00:13:45,574 --> 00:13:46,534
Aah!

163
00:13:46,617 --> 00:13:49,036
[hisses] Aah!

164
00:13:50,788 --> 00:13:52,206
[sniffles]

165
00:13:53,457 --> 00:13:54,833
[cries]

166
00:13:55,834 --> 00:13:57,044
[sniffles]

167
00:13:57,127 --> 00:13:59,213
[breathes heavily]

168
00:14:00,798 --> 00:14:02,091
Don't worry…

169
00:14:06,428 --> 00:14:07,846
I'll avenge you.

170
00:14:10,057 --> 00:14:11,016
Lara…

171
00:14:13,143 --> 00:14:14,770
Forgive me.

172
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:18,107
I'll avenge you. [cries]

173
00:14:18,732 --> 00:14:20,109
[sniffles]

174
00:14:20,192 --> 00:14:24,864
[crying, sobbing]

175
00:14:25,364 --> 00:14:27,366
- [exhales deeply, screams]
- [slams]

176
00:14:27,449 --> 00:14:28,701
[wailing]

177
00:14:29,910 --> 00:14:36,417
[breathing heavily]

178
00:14:40,963 --> 00:14:43,257
[groans]

179
00:15:03,777 --> 00:15:08,532
[tense music playing]

180
00:15:36,268 --> 00:15:37,645
Where is it?

181
00:15:43,859 --> 00:15:45,945
[stirring music playing]

182
00:15:51,450 --> 00:15:54,078
[Felix] Who did this to Madam?!

183
00:15:54,161 --> 00:15:57,206
Who's responsible for this, huh?! [sobs]

184
00:15:57,790 --> 00:15:59,917
- What happened?
- [Felix] Madam!

185
00:16:00,501 --> 00:16:03,087
- Madam! [sobs]
- [Liam] Courageous.

186
00:16:04,546 --> 00:16:06,340
Sir. Sir, what happened?

187
00:16:07,466 --> 00:16:08,509
Where is Lara, sir?

188
00:16:08,592 --> 00:16:10,928
Haven't you received the information yet?

189
00:16:12,054 --> 00:16:15,683
Agent Angeles was found last night
in front of the NLEA.

190
00:16:15,766 --> 00:16:17,685
[unsettling music playing]

191
00:16:17,768 --> 00:16:19,645
Wrapped in a body bag.

192
00:16:20,270 --> 00:16:21,438
Dead!

193
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:28,362
Who would do this to Agent Angeles?

194
00:16:32,324 --> 00:16:33,701
Who do you think?

195
00:16:34,618 --> 00:16:37,955
[unsettling music continues]

196
00:16:59,476 --> 00:17:01,520
[Carillo] Where is Lara?!

197
00:17:01,603 --> 00:17:04,106
Where is my daughter?

198
00:17:05,107 --> 00:17:08,402
[wailing] Lara!

199
00:17:08,485 --> 00:17:10,070
My child!

200
00:17:10,154 --> 00:17:12,406
Stop! Where's my daughter?

201
00:17:12,489 --> 00:17:16,410
[Carillo] Who did this? Who did this?

202
00:17:16,493 --> 00:17:19,455
- They must pay!
- [Villanueva] General!

203
00:17:19,538 --> 00:17:22,499
We send our condolences, General.
We will get to the bottom of this.

204
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:24,168
[Carillo] Shut up!

205
00:17:24,251 --> 00:17:27,629
You cops are all useless!

206
00:17:27,713 --> 00:17:30,007
You couldn't even protect Lara!

207
00:17:30,090 --> 00:17:35,721
[Carillo wailing]

208
00:17:36,305 --> 00:17:38,682
[Carillo] Lara!

209
00:17:38,766 --> 00:17:40,684
[stirring music continues]

210
00:17:40,768 --> 00:17:43,437
[Carillo sobbing] Lara!

211
00:17:43,520 --> 00:17:46,440
Why are you all just staring?

212
00:17:46,523 --> 00:17:48,859
Do something!

213
00:17:48,942 --> 00:17:51,028
[sobbing]

214
00:18:00,621 --> 00:18:02,706
Whoever did this…

215
00:18:13,967 --> 00:18:15,302
[pensive music playing]

216
00:18:15,385 --> 00:18:16,970
Based on the initial report…

217
00:18:17,679 --> 00:18:19,306
she only had a single gunshot wound…

218
00:18:19,389 --> 00:18:21,642
in her torso area near the heart.

219
00:18:22,267 --> 00:18:23,310
Fatal.

220
00:18:23,393 --> 00:18:26,146
But if there were no defensive wounds

221
00:18:26,688 --> 00:18:27,940
or signs of struggle…

222
00:18:29,149 --> 00:18:30,359
that means she wasn't kidnapped.

223
00:18:30,442 --> 00:18:31,693
I agree.

224
00:18:31,777 --> 00:18:33,570
Because if she was kidnapped,
it's impossible that

225
00:18:33,654 --> 00:18:35,030
Agent Angeles won't fight back.

226
00:18:35,697 --> 00:18:37,366
[Ryan] So she was really targeted?

227
00:18:38,242 --> 00:18:39,660
Assassination.

228
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:42,454
Or what if she was also shot by a sniper?

229
00:18:43,163 --> 00:18:44,540
No.

230
00:18:44,623 --> 00:18:47,167
It was a handgun
based on the initial analysis.

231
00:18:47,251 --> 00:18:48,544
She was shot at close range.

232
00:18:48,627 --> 00:18:50,045
[grim music playing]

233
00:18:50,629 --> 00:18:55,259
[sighs] The number of our teammates
getting killed is increasing.

234
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:58,470
[Sean] But I still can't believe
that Ma'am Lara is already gone.

235
00:19:08,272 --> 00:19:09,606
[Ethan] Agent Reyes, sir.

236
00:19:09,690 --> 00:19:10,983
[Marcus] What's the update?

237
00:19:11,066 --> 00:19:13,944
We already checked the CCTV footage.

238
00:19:14,027 --> 00:19:15,279
Did you find anything?

239
00:19:15,362 --> 00:19:16,321
[Buster] Nothing, sir.

240
00:19:16,405 --> 00:19:19,491
The body bag was dropped
at the security camera's blind spot.

241
00:19:19,575 --> 00:19:22,161
The person who dropped it
seems to know the entire perimeter.

242
00:19:22,244 --> 00:19:26,165
[suspenseful music playing]

243
00:19:33,881 --> 00:19:35,340
[cameras shuttering]

244
00:19:35,424 --> 00:19:37,759
[Carillo sighs deeply] I can't accept it.

245
00:19:39,178 --> 00:19:40,137
Why?

246
00:19:40,637 --> 00:19:43,015
Why was my daughter killed?

247
00:19:45,225 --> 00:19:47,227
[Carillo] <i>She was a good person.</i>

248
00:19:47,311 --> 00:19:49,354
<i>She didn't deserve this.</i>

249
00:19:49,438 --> 00:19:50,731
[stirring music playing]

250
00:19:53,150 --> 00:19:55,944
<i>Lara was very special to me.</i>

251
00:19:57,821 --> 00:20:01,450
She was just a kid when I saved her

252
00:20:02,034 --> 00:20:04,745
<i>from the crime syndicate</i>
<i>that abducted her.</i>

253
00:20:04,828 --> 00:20:06,038
[Carillo] <i>Uh…</i>

254
00:20:06,663 --> 00:20:11,210
<i>That was after her parents died.</i>

255
00:20:11,293 --> 00:20:15,505
[Carillo sniffles]

256
00:20:15,589 --> 00:20:20,636
We eventually found out
the more painful truth…

257
00:20:21,220 --> 00:20:27,059
that Lara's parents
were actually killed by terrorists.

258
00:20:27,142 --> 00:20:30,062
[foreboding music playing]

259
00:20:32,522 --> 00:20:36,818
[Carillo] That became
her guiding principle…

260
00:20:37,444 --> 00:20:39,446
until she grew up.

261
00:20:40,030 --> 00:20:40,906
[sobbing]

262
00:20:41,448 --> 00:20:43,617
Ever since she was a kid, she really…

263
00:20:44,159 --> 00:20:48,247
She already wanted to be an SID agent.

264
00:20:48,830 --> 00:20:52,626
[Carillo] <i>She wanted to protect and save</i>

265
00:20:53,168 --> 00:20:56,004
<i>kids like her.</i>

266
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:59,383
<i>Children who were victims of…</i>

267
00:21:01,176 --> 00:21:02,386
violence.

268
00:21:02,928 --> 00:21:05,264
[Carillo sighs deeply]

269
00:21:05,347 --> 00:21:07,099
<i>But in the end…</i>

270
00:21:07,182 --> 00:21:11,979
her life would also end
because of violence.

271
00:21:12,062 --> 00:21:15,732
[foreboding music continues]

272
00:21:22,531 --> 00:21:27,494
So to whoever did this,
you better be ready.

273
00:21:28,036 --> 00:21:34,876
I won't stop until you pay
for what you've done!

274
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:37,337
[foreboding music continues]

275
00:21:48,932 --> 00:21:50,267
Father…

276
00:21:50,976 --> 00:21:54,730
Wasn't she the woman
who attacked you here in the house?

277
00:21:56,440 --> 00:21:59,318
She was killed right after
she found out the truth.

278
00:21:59,401 --> 00:22:03,655
[suspenseful music playing]

279
00:22:03,739 --> 00:22:07,576
The crime syndicate
could be behind that, right, Father?

280
00:22:09,953 --> 00:22:11,580
I don't know, dear.

281
00:22:12,456 --> 00:22:13,957
But that's possible.

282
00:22:14,666 --> 00:22:18,170
The people behind that syndicate
are powerful.

283
00:22:19,463 --> 00:22:22,299
They can do whatever they want.

284
00:22:22,382 --> 00:22:24,176
[suspenseful music continues]

285
00:22:47,449 --> 00:22:52,037
[music turns pensive]

286
00:22:54,206 --> 00:22:55,624
[Carillo sighs]

287
00:22:58,376 --> 00:22:59,294
Felix…

288
00:23:03,173 --> 00:23:04,758
[breathes deeply]

289
00:23:05,383 --> 00:23:06,927
I know that…

290
00:23:07,469 --> 00:23:09,262
you love Lara.

291
00:23:10,764 --> 00:23:12,557
But because of what you did…

292
00:23:14,476 --> 00:23:16,812
you've proven to me…

293
00:23:17,562 --> 00:23:19,564
your loyalty.

294
00:23:19,648 --> 00:23:23,193
[stirring music playing]

295
00:23:23,819 --> 00:23:25,028
[inhales sharply]

296
00:23:25,612 --> 00:23:27,781
[Manuel exhales deeply]

297
00:24:00,272 --> 00:24:01,940
[Espina] <i>Farewell, Agent Angeles.</i>

298
00:24:02,023 --> 00:24:04,776
[Felix] <i>Madam is no longer with us.</i>
<i>She's really gone.</i>

299
00:24:04,860 --> 00:24:05,735
I'm sorry.

300
00:24:05,819 --> 00:24:06,570
[action music playing]

301
00:24:06,653 --> 00:24:09,865
But we have to watch Felix from now on.

302
00:24:09,948 --> 00:24:13,952
[Espina] <i>We don't know</i>
<i>who we can trust among our people.</i>

303
00:24:14,536 --> 00:24:17,706
General Carillo was also involved
in Lara's death.

304
00:24:17,789 --> 00:24:20,750
How can a parent do that
to their own child?

305
00:24:20,834 --> 00:24:24,254
Is the problem
with a lack of law enforcement

306
00:24:24,337 --> 00:24:28,550
<i>or is there a bigger reason</i>
<i>that we have not seen yet?</i>

307
00:24:28,633 --> 00:24:31,761
Someone wants to overthrow the government?

308
00:24:31,845 --> 00:24:34,890
General Carillo can explain
destabilization himself

309
00:24:34,973 --> 00:24:37,184
because that's his expertise.

310
00:24:38,018 --> 00:24:43,815
This all started
when MV Doña Emilia exploded.

311
00:24:43,899 --> 00:24:44,858
["Maninindigan" by Marko Rudio playing]

312
00:24:44,941 --> 00:24:47,652
Are you convinced
that it wasn't an accident, sir?

313
00:24:47,736 --> 00:24:48,862
Why do you ask?

314
00:24:49,446 --> 00:24:51,323
[Marcus] <i>Because that's where</i>
<i>my brother died, sir.</i>

315
00:24:51,406 --> 00:24:56,244
♪ <i>Will not retreat</i>
<i>Will fight and stand firm</i> ♪
